!Alert macro and class attribute

Alet macro has a `class` attribute lets pass extra css classes to customize it.  Any CSS relevant classes can be used, but mostly customized classes are used for this purpose. In Shiraz 2.0+ these classes are courtesy from Bootstrap and can be found in [[demo/bootstrap-classes]].

!! Examples i
See below examples. Two classes are used here! `leftbar` which adds a left thick border and `border-primary` (or other conceptual colors, see [[demo/contextual-classes]]) which adds color to left border.

```
<<alert primary src:"Leftbar alert primary" class:"leftbar border-primary">>
<<alert danger src:"Leftbar alert danger" class:"leftbar border-danger">>
<<alert success src:"Leftbar alert success" class:"leftbar border-success">>
<<alert warning src:"Leftbar alert warning" class:"leftbar border-warning">>
<<alert info src:"Leftbar alert info" class:"leftbar border-info">>
<<alert secondary src:"Leftbar alert secondary" class:"leftbar border-secondary">>
<<alert dark src:"Leftbar alert dark" class:"leftbar border-dark">>
```
