!Examples ii

Here the class `border-` e.g. `border-primary` is used to create alerts with full colored borders.

```
<<alert primary src:"Primary" class:"border-primary">>
<<alert danger src:"Danger" class:"border-danger">>
<<alert warning src:"Warning" class:"border-warning">>
<<alert info src:"Info" class:"border-info">>
```

<<alert primary src:"Primary" class:"border-primary">>
<<alert danger src:"Danger" class:"border-danger">>
<<alert warning src:"Warning" class:"border-warning">>
<<alert info src:"Info" class:"border-info">>


!!Examples iii

Here `bg-transparent` class is used to create alerts with colored text and borders and no background.

```
<$macrocall $name="alert" type="primary" src=<<.lorem>> class="bg-transparent"/>
<$macrocall $name="alert" type="danger" src=<<.lorem>> class="bg-transparent"/>
```

